Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: no, I do not believe in making current events a priority.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: feeding and clothing their families, paying their bills, etc.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: who are neglecting their real responsibilities are spending more time online in social networks, and paying more attention to current events as a result.

actions.text: actually making them worse, given that they are neglecting their legitimate duties.

actions.text: the good citizen, simply being one who cares enough about society to get informed on what is going on in the world, and then asking questions and speaking

actions.text: in today's world, with contemporary technology and institutions, I suspect that the achievement of such a citizen is becoming more and more difficult.
